line.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/law-and-order-organized-crime-season-5-episode-8-recap-headset.jpg?resize=640,427 640w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/law-and-order-organized-crime-season-5-episode-8-recap-headset.jpg?resize=800,534 800w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1259px) 100vw, 1259px\"/\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003e \u003ccite\u003eCourtesy of Peacock\u003c/cite\u003e\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eI’d like to note that, by this point in the episode, a worried and distracted Stabler has slept roughly five minutes (if that) in the previous 48 hours. He’s running on adrenaline, cortisol and bodega coffee: THIS is the man we want pawing at the bomb’s complicated keypad as Vargas coaches him from the van?\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eRegardless, Vargas manages to beat A.G. and The Collective by using his code, which they co-opted, against them. By the time A.G. orders the explosion, the device is inactive, and Tanner is safe. She hugs Stabler in relief as he helps her stand, then she takes off — ostensibly to pee, given how she mentioned her full bladder a few scenes back.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eWith that crisis averted, the New York Police Department rolls in and arrests A.G. and the rest of his murderous Collective.\n\n\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1259\" height=\"840\" src=\"https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/law-and-order-organized-crime-season-5-episode-8-recap-bernie.jpg?w=650\" alt=\"law-and-order-organized-crime-season-5-episode-8-recap \" srcset=\"https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/law-and-order-organized-crime-season-5-episode-8-recap-bernie.jpg 1259w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/law-and-order-organized-crime-season-5-episode-8-recap-bernie.jpg?resize=200,133 200w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/law-and-order-organized-crime-season-5-episode-8-recap-bernie.jpg?resize=300,200 300w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/law-and-order-organized-crime-season-5-episode-8-recap-bernie.jpg?resize=768,512 768w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/law-and-order-organized-crime-season-5-episode-8-recap-bernie.jpg?resize=1024,683 1024w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/law-and-order-organized-crime-season-5-episode-8-recap-bernie.jpg?resize=150,100 150w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/law-and-order-organized-crime-season-5-episode-8-recap-bernie.jpg?resize=600,400 600w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/law-and-order-organized-crime-season-5-episode-8-recap-bernie.jpg?resize=280,187 280w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/law-and-order-organized-crime-season-5-episode-8-recap-bernie.jpg?resize=1000,667 1000w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/law-and-order-organized-crime-season-5-episode-8-recap-bernie.jpg?resize=244,163 244w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/law-and-order-organized-crime-season-5-episode-8-recap-bernie.jpg?resize=1160,774 1160w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/law-and-order-organized-crime-season-5-episode-8-recap-bernie.jpg?resize=900,600 900w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/law-and-order-organized-crime-season-5-episode-8-recap-bernie.jpg?resize=142,95 142w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/law-and-order-organized-crime-season-5-episode-8-recap-bernie.jpg?resize=60,40 60w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/law-and-order-organized-crime-season-5-episode-8-recap-bernie.jpg?resize=50,33 50w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/law-and-order-organized-crime-season-5-episode-8-recap-bernie.jpg?resize=1200,801 1200w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/law-and-order-organized-crime-season-5-episode-8-recap-bernie.jpg?resize=42,28 42w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/law-and-order-organized-crime-season-5-episode-8-recap-bernie.jpg?resize=252,168 252w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/law-and-order-organized-crime-season-5-episode-8-recap-bernie.jpg?resize=505,337 505w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/law-and-order-organized-crime-season-5-episode-8-recap-bernie.jpg?resize=1012,675 1012w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/law-and-order-organized-crime-season-5-episode-8-recap-bernie.jpg?resize=37,25 37w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/law-and-order-organized-crime-season-5-episode-8-recap-bernie.jpg?resize=225,150 225w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/law-and-order-organized-crime-season-5-episode-8-recap-bernie.jpg?resize=450,300 450w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/law-and-order-organized-crime-season-5-episode-8-recap-bernie.jpg?resize=899,600 899w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/law-and-order-organized-crime-season-5-episode-8-recap-bernie.jpg?resize=110,73 110w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/law-and-order-organized-crime-season-5-episode-8-recap-bernie.jpg?resize=285,190 285w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/law-and-order-organized-crime-season-5-episode-8-recap-bernie.jpg?resize=320,214 320w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/law-and-order-organized-crime-season-5-episode-8-recap-bernie.jpg?resize=640,427 640w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/law-and-order-organized-crime-season-5-episode-8-recap-bernie.jpg?resize=800,534 800w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1259px) 100vw, 1259px\"/\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003e \u003ccite\u003eCourtesy of Peacock\u003c/cite\u003e\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eIS JOE JR. A DEAD MAN?\u003c/strong\u003e | On to Bernie, whose story starts in a very scary way: Randall finds his elderly mother, on the floor and gasping for air, when he comes home from the store. The issue turns out to be a problem with her heart, and while she’s in surgery for a cardiac ablation, the Stablers — including Kathleen — take turns keeping vigil in the waiting room.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eElliot uses the time to let Randall know how grateful he is for his help with their mom, and to tell his brother how much he’s missed him. Kathleen uses the time to make sure her father knows his mother is not long for this world — even under the best of outcomes — and that he should probably make his peace with that fact sooner rather than later. (It should surprise no one that Elliot quite literally gives it to God during this conversation and keeps things moving.)  \u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1259\" height=\"840\" src=\"https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/law-and-order-organized-crime-season-5-episode-8-recap-randall.jpg?w=650\" alt=\"law-and-order-organized-crime-season-5-episode-8-recap\" srcset=\"https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/law-and-order-organized-crime-season-5-episode-8-recap-randall.jpg 1259w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/law-and-order-organized-crime-season-5-episode-8-recap-randall.jpg?resize=200,133 200w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/law-and-order-organized-crime-season-5-episode-8-recap-randall.jpg?resize=300,200 300w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/law-and-order-organized-crime-season-5-episode-8-recap-randall.jpg?resize=768,512 768w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/law-and-order-organized-crime-season-5-episode-8-recap-randall.jpg?resize=1024,683 1024w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/law-and-order-organized-crime-season-5-episode-8-recap-randall.jpg?resize=150,100 150w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/law-and-order-organized-crime-season-5-episode-8-recap-randall.jpg?resize=600,400 600w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/law-and-order-organized-crime-season-5-episode-8-recap-randall.jpg?resize=280,187 280w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/law-and-order-organized-crime-season-5-episode-8-recap-randall.jpg?resize=1000,667 1000w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/law-and-order-organized-crime-season-5-episode-8-recap-randall.jpg?resize=244,163 244w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/law-and-order-organized-crime-season-5-episode-8-recap-randall.jpg?resize=1160,774 1160w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/law-and-order-organized-crime-season-5-episode-8-recap-randall.jpg?resize=900,600 900w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/law-and-order-organized-crime-season-5-episode-8-recap-randall.jpg?resize=142,95 142w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/law-and-order-organized-crime-season-5-episode-8-recap-randall.jpg?resize=60,40 60w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/law-and-order-organized-crime-season-5-episode-8-recap-randall.jpg?resize=50,33 50w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/law-and-order-organized-crime-season-5-episode-8-recap-randall.jpg?resize=1200,801 1200w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/law-and-order-organized-crime-season-5-episode-8-recap-randall.jpg?resize=42,28 42w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/law-and-order-organized-crime-season-5-episode-8-recap-randall.jpg?resize=252,168 252w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/law-and-order-organized-crime-season-5-episode-8-recap-randall.jpg?resize=505,337 505w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/law-and-order-organized-crime-season-5-episode-8-recap-randall.jpg?resize=1012,675 1012w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/law-and-order-organized-crime-season-5-episode-8-recap-randall.jpg?resize=37,25 37w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/law-and-order-organized-crime-season-5-episode-8-recap-randall.jpg?resize=225,150 225w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/law-and-order-organized-crime-season-5-episode-8-recap-randall.jpg?resize=450,300 450w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/law-and-order-organized-crime-season-5-episode-8-recap-randall.jpg?resize=899,600 899w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/law-and-order-organized-crime-season-5-episode-8-recap-randall.jpg?resize=110,73 110w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/law-and-order-organized-crime-season-5-episode-8-recap-randall.jpg?resize=285,190 285w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/law-and-order-organized-crime-season-5-episode-8-recap-randall.jpg?resize=320,214 320w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/law-and-order-organized-crime-season-5-episode-8-recap-randall.jpg?resize=640,427 640w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/law-and-order-organized-crime-season-5-episode-8-recap-randall.jpg?resize=800,534 800w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1259px) 100vw, 1259px\"/\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003e \u003ccite\u003eCourtesy of Peacock\u003c/cite\u003e\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eAt one point, Randall is dozing next to his mother’s bed when he wakes to see a bad bleach job in scrubs hightailing it out of the room. Yep, it’s Joey, doing his Snuffleupagus act again; Randall chases him but the younger Stabler is too quick and slips away.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eIn the episode’s final minutes, though, Stabler gets a call: It’s Joe Jr., checking in on Bernie. “Listen: No matter what happens — and it’s going to happen soon, Elliot — know that I love you,” he says. “I made my own choices.” Instantly concerned, Stabler promises that he can help his brother get out of whatever trouble he’s in. “Just know that I love you,” Joey repeats, hanging up just before he’s picked up by a sleek black SUV somewhere in New York City.\n\n\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eKathleen, who’s overheard her father’s side of the call, looks on with wide eyes: “Grandma was right!”\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eNow it’s your turn. What did you think about the episode? Are the Stablers in for a world of hurt before the end of the season? Hit the comments, and let us know!\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
